reviews.review_text:
WOWOWOWOW! i am utterly surprised that the number of reviews for this show is none, Black Peter > ; Garcia is soloing left and right and up and down for the last 3 min of the track. all in all the show is screamin sound, and filled with energy a great addition to any library, and a gem from 89.

as for the quality of recording, for a windy day not half bad, i have no complaints, just plug your nose take a big bite chew and swallow...
Static Watch out for the static in Stranger.

franklin's surprising that none of you heads commented with regard to Jerry treating the trip nuggets with a slide outtro in Franklin's- a sweet little seque in walkin!  sans for the static in stranger- a solid show!

Great Sound I am streaming this right now and it is smokin' IMHO. Phil is nice and loud in the mix and Jerry and Brent are both sounding exceptionally sweet as well as the others. At the half way point I would give this 4-5 stars. Aloha to the band and all who helped bring this treasure to us. Many, many, thanks. I am a 50 year old kid in a candy store . I can't believe how great this site is.  Peace and Kindness to all.
